# Phase System

## No Hardcoded Enums

Phases are **not** enums. They are created generically per arena via [PhaseProvider].

## Main Phases

- Created per arena by [PhaseProvider.createPhases]
- Ordered by [priority]; Core advances sequentially (nextPhase = priority + 1)
- Typical sequence: Map Voting → Game Voting → In-Game Lobby → In-Game → Ending
- Each arena can have a custom phase configuration

## Sub-Phases (Playing Phase Only)

- Each [MicroGame] defines its own via [MicroGame.createPlayingSubPhases]
- Examples: Spleef → "building", "fighting"; TNT Run → "countdown", "running"
- [ArenaContext.currentSubPhase] is non-null only when in In-Game phase
- Games advance via [ArenaContext.advanceToNextSubPhase]

## Key Types

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [Phase] | Main phase interface (id, name, priority, start, stop) |
| [SubPhase] | Sub-phase within Playing (game-specific) |
| [PhaseProvider] | Creates phase list per arena |
| [PhaseId] / [SubPhaseId] | Value class identifiers |

## Reference

Pattern: phases per arena (Multimap<ArenaId, Phase>), priority-based advancement, Playing phase holds game-specific sub-phases.
